-- Gazprom-Media Holding Boosts 2012 Revenue 11% to $1.7 Billion
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2013-03-29T07:22:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-29/gazprom-media-holding-boosts-2012-revenue-11-to-1-7-billion.html
Gazprom-Media Holding,  Russia ’s
largest media company, increased revenue 11 percent last year to
52.3 billion rubles ($1.7 billion), according to a  statement  on
its website.  Net income rose 36 percent to 7.7 billion rubles, Gazprom-
Media said. The company runs the NTV and TNT television
channels, pay-TV operator NTV Plus, radio stations including
Echo of Moscow and magazines including 7Days.  Gazprom-Media is controlled by Gazprombank, which is part-
owned by Russia’s largest natural gas producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
